big brother sing in a choir?

11:00.360 --> 11:02.830
[door opens, closes]

11:02.863 --> 11:05.165
Okay.
[sighs]

11:05.198 --> 11:07.400
Cash!
You're a child.

11:07.434 --> 11:09.069
Anjali's a child, too.

11:09.102 --> 11:11.038
Why don't you two go play
in my office?

11:11.071 --> 11:12.472
- Actually, I--

11:12.505 --> 11:14.374
- Wouldn't want
to disappoint God?

11:14.407 --> 11:17.310
[country-tinged holiday music]

11:17.344 --> 11:21.248
*

11:21.281 --> 11:23.016
- Can I try?

11:23.050 --> 11:24.718
- I mean, I guess.

11:24.752 --> 11:26.987
It's kind of complicated,
though.

11:27.020 --> 11:29.589
[gunshots and screaming
on video game]

11:29.622 --> 11:32.559
Did you just make
a pipe bomb out of a sneaker?

11:32.592 --> 11:35.328
I didn't know
you could do that.

11:35.362 --> 11:37.497
- How do I get one of these?
- I don't know.

11:37.530 --> 11:39.699
Ask Santa.
- Who?

11:39.733 --> 11:42.435
- You don't know
who Santa is?

11:42.469 --> 11:45.038
I'm about
to blow your mind.

11:45.072 --> 11:47.775
- Athanasios, you like music.

11:47.808 --> 11:50.543
Come to the Christmas concert
on Friday.

11:50.577 --> 11:53.747
- Ah.
No, thank you.

11:53.781 --> 11:55.682
- A little less
second-grade teacher,

11:55.715 --> 11:57.417
a little more "Godfather."

11:57.450 --> 12:00.020
Make him an offer
he can't refuse.

12:00.053 --> 12:02.722
Hey, isn't your family in town?
- They are.

12:02.756 --> 12:05.125
- Bring them to the concert,
and I'll give you a day off.

12:05.158 --> 12:08.796
- Throw in Greek Easter and my
yia-yia's birthday, and I'm in.

12:08.829 --> 12:10.463
- You drive a hard bargain.
- Hmm.

12:12.933 --> 12:14.434
- He should've held out.

12:14.467 --> 12:17.070
I was gonna
give him health insurance.

12:17.104 --> 12:18.939
- I am so excited
about this concert.

12:18.972 --> 12:21.641
I just hope I can whip
the choir into shape by Friday.

12:21.674 --> 12:23.743
- Ask Santa for help.
- What?

12:23.777 --> 12:25.612
[chuckles awkwardly]
Santa? Who's that?

12:25.645 --> 12:27.580
No one, that's who.
- You've never heard of Santa?

12:27.614 --> 12:29.149
He's just like Jesus,

12:29.182 --> 12:31.084
but he rewards people who
behave righteously with toys.

12:31.118 --> 12:33.053
- Interesting--
they are kind of similar,

12:33.086 --> 12:34.587
aside from the obvious
weight difference.

12:34.621 --> 12:37.124
- No, he's nothing
like Jesus, okay?

12:37.157 --> 12:39.126
- So did you two have fun?
- So much fun.

12:39.159 --> 12:40.627
I learned about Santa.

12:40.660 --> 12:42.629
He's gonna bring me this game
called "Murder Car,"

12:42.662 --> 12:44.597
where you kill people
and then steal their cars.

12:44.631 --> 12:46.299
- There's also prostitutes.
- [gasping]

12:46.333 --> 12:48.768
- What?
What can I talk about?

12:48.802 --> 12:51.604
- Jax--sweetheart, your brother
has led you astray.

12:54.374 --> 12:56.643
- [sighs]
That was so fun,

12:56.676 --> 12:59.913
I am not even gonna eat
my feelings about it later.

12:59.947 --> 13:01.681
- That's good, 'cause Dwayne
only eats rabbit food.

13:01.714 --> 13:02.816
- [chuckles]

13:02.850 --> 13:04.517
Ew, gross!

13:04.551 --> 13:06.486
I thought you gave up
chewing tobacco.

13:06.519 --> 13:08.321
- Oh.
- Oh.

13:08.355 --> 13:10.190
[objects rattle]

13:11.959 --> 13:14.194
[gasps]
That's my birthstone.

13:14.227 --> 13:16.496
- Mm-hmm.

13:16.529 --> 13:18.265
- What happened to no strings?

13:18.298 --> 13:21.468
- Yeah, see, I don't think
I can do no strings,

13:21.501 --> 13:23.703
especially with you,

13:23.736 --> 13:25.605
'cause I never wanted
to break our strings.

13:25.638 --> 13:27.807
- Whoa.

13:27.841 --> 13:29.509
I need to think about this.

13:29.542 --> 13:30.710
- I understand.
It's a lot.

13:30.743 --> 13:32.179
- Mm-hmm.
- I'll take 'em back.

13:32.212 --> 13:33.646
- Whoa, no.
You just gave 'em to me.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.782
No backsies.
- They're real, too.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.650
They won't turn your ear green
or nothing.

13:39.920 --> 13:42.655
- So, Barb, what are you doing
this Friday?

13:42.689 --> 13:45.558
- I'm going to
the Wildcats game, obviously.

13:45.592 --> 13:49.496
- It would mean a lot if you
came to the Christmas concert.

13:49.529 --> 13:52.632
- Can I have a solo?
- You're not in the choir.

13:52.665 --> 13:55.969
- Can I be in the choir?
- Um...

13:56.003 --> 13:58.205
If you bring
three friends, sure.

13:58.238 --> 14:00.040
- All right.

14:00.073 --> 14:03.676
- Ah, please tell me Wayne
didn't buy you those earrings.

14:03.710 --> 14:05.412
- He's a new man.

14:05.445 --> 14:07.414
They're the first gift he gave
me that I don't have to feed.

14:07.447 --> 14:10.183
- You know Wayne
better than I do.

14:10.217 --> 14:12.552
- Mm-hmm.
- So you'd know how a man

14:12.585 --> 14:14.554
who tries to pay his tab
in snake eggs

14:14.587 --> 14:16.223
would be able to
afford fancy earrings.

14:16.256 --> 14:18.725
- I don't have to ask.
I trust him.

14:18.758 --> 14:22.595
- Trust him enough to still
have a joint bank account?

14:22.629 --> 14:25.565
[suspicious music]

14:25.598 --> 14:29.836
*

14:29.869 --> 14:32.705
- [gasps]
Son of a B!

14:32.739 --> 14:33.907
[groans]

14:35.542 --> 14:37.010
- Where's Mom and Dad?

14:37.044 --> 14:38.845
- They're in the back recording
a sermon for YouTube.

14:38.878 --> 14:41.848
I'm sure it's
"prodigal son" related.

14:41.881 --> 14:44.384
You sure love the Bible,
don't you?

14:44.417 --> 14:45.852
- Well, we move around a lot.

14:45.885 --> 14:47.454
It's one thing
I can always count on.

14:47.487 --> 14:49.456
- It's not easy bouncing around
all the time.

14:49.489 --> 14:52.025
[chuckles] I used to sneak away
and watch movies.

14:52.059 --> 14:54.061
You should've seen
the look on Dad's face

14:54.094 --> 14:56.363
when he caught me watching "If
Rosemary had Baptized her Baby,

14:56.396 --> 14:57.897
None of This
Would've Happened."

14:57.931 --> 15:00.033
- I used to love
watching movies.

15:00.067 --> 15:02.202
I watched them all the time
back in India.

15:02.235 --> 15:03.370
- What was your favorite?

15:03.403 --> 15:05.138
- Anything
with Priyanka Chopra.

15:05.172 --> 15:06.940
- I love her.
- Her Bollywood stuff.

15:06.974 --> 15:08.575
Not the lifeguard movie called

15:08.608 --> 15:10.477
"Running Around
in Red Swimsuits is a Sin."

15:10.510 --> 15:12.912
- Would it be all right
if I tousled your hair?

15:12.946 --> 15:14.948
- I'd rather you didn't.
- And that's why I asked.

15:14.982 --> 15:16.683
[chuckles awkwardly]

15:18.118 --> 15:20.887
- That was nice.
Except for that hair tousle.

15:20.920 --> 15:22.622
That was weird.
- It felt weird.

15:22.655 --> 15:24.224
- Yeah, it creeped me out.

15:24.257 --> 15:26.126
- Do you think my parents
will get mad

15:26.159 --> 15:28.395
about the whole movie thing?

15:28.428 --> 15:31.464
- What, you connected with her.
You--you made her smile.

15:31.498 --> 15:33.433
Isn't that what church
is all about?

15:33.466 --> 15:35.602
- Could you repeat that
when my parents are around

15:35.635 --> 15:38.671
so they know I successfully
ministered to an atheist?

15:38.705 --> 15:40.673
- Jax, forget about
what your parents think.

15:40.707 --> 15:43.143
This is your church.

15:43.176 --> 15:45.945
You need to think about
how you want to reach people.

15:47.647 --> 15:50.117
We have 24 hours
before the concert.

15:50.150 --> 15:53.020
What do you say--you want
to Jax it up a little bit?

15:53.053 --> 15:56.589
- Maybe, but it'll still be
to an empty church.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.691
- You worry about the music.
I'll worry about the crowd.

15:58.725 --> 16:00.994
Actually, I'll worry
about the music and the crowd.

16:01.028 --> 16:02.795
- Can someone take this?

16:02.829 --> 16:05.765
I don't want to be seen
with a big pair of scissors.

16:05.798 --> 16:07.767
People project aggression
onto men of my stature.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.136
- Don't pass them to me.

16:09.169 --> 16:10.637
I can't look my friends
in the eye

16:10.670 --> 16:11.938
knowing I cut off
the UK game.

16:11.971 --> 16:13.440
- Come on, give it to me.

16:13.473 --> 16:15.775
The only thing people project
on me is privilege.

16:15.808 --> 16:19.979
Remember, after all,
this is for Jax.

16:20.013 --> 16:21.681
- It's this one right here.

16:21.714 --> 16:24.551
I appreciate you making such
a huge sacrifice for a friend.

16:24.584 --> 16:25.985
- What sacrifice?

16:26.019 --> 16:27.320
- This is
the Internet connection

16:27.354 --> 16:28.721
as well as the cable.

16:28.755 --> 16:30.323
You're cutting off our chances
to broadcast the concert

16:30.357 --> 16:31.958
on YouTube.

16:31.991 --> 16:35.028
- Torn between a return to
relevance

16:35.062 --> 16:36.863
and helping a weirdo
in a cardigan

16:36.896 --> 16:38.998
who I didn't even know
four months ago.

16:39.032 --> 16:40.733
- He looks really cute
in that cardigan, though.

16:40.767 --> 16:42.302
- Damn it.

16:42.335 --> 16:44.137
He does.

16:44.171 --> 16:46.173
[electricity whirs off]
Let's go!

16:46.206 --> 16:48.007
Go, go!
- Got it.

16:48.041 --> 16:49.909
- [humming innocently]

16:54.747 --> 16:56.383
- There you are.

16:56.416 --> 16:57.917
Did you take money
from our joint account

16:57.950 --> 16:58.985
to buy those earrings?

16:59.018 --> 17:01.020
- Part of it, yeah,

17:01.054 --> 17:02.989
but then the rest I invested
in my buddy Dookie's business.

17:03.022 --> 17:05.024
- I can't believe
I thought you changed.

17:05.058 --> 17:07.060
This is something the old Wayne
would've done,

17:07.094 --> 17:09.396
and in case you forgot,
he's the one I'm divorcing.

17:09.429 --> 17:11.098
- It's a can't-miss.

17:11.131 --> 17:13.100
He's turning
Tracy Chapman lyrics

17:13.133 --> 17:15.568
into inspirational towels.

17:17.237 --> 17:19.506
- Take these back.

17:19.539 --> 17:20.740
I think it's best we start

17:20.773 --> 17:22.675
our New Year's resolution
early this year.

17:22.709 --> 17:24.277
- Oh, but, Jenny...

17:24.311 --> 17:26.579
Tracy Chapman's
never been hotter.

17:26.613 --> 17:28.081
This is her year.

17:28.115 --> 17:29.549
[indistinct chatter]

17:29.582 --> 17:31.284
- Look at this crowd.

17:31.318 --> 17:33.253
We haven't had this many people
since Google Maps

17:33.286 --> 17:36.289
accidentally listed us
as a "Second First Churros."

17:36.323 --> 17:37.957
[indistinct chatter]

17:37.990 --> 17:39.859
- What is Barb doing here?

17:39.892 --> 17:41.728
- Oh, she's in the choir now,
and she has a solo.

17:41.761 --> 17:44.797
- What?
- Go with it.

17:44.831 --> 17:47.134
- [sighs]
Good evening, everyone!

17:47.167 --> 17:49.569
Welcome to The Second First
Church of the Cumberlands.

17:49.602 --> 17:51.704
I, of course, am
world-renowned choir director

17:51.738 --> 17:53.140
Dr. Arthur Cochran.

17:53.173 --> 17:55.108
I have worked
with bigger choirs.

17:55.142 --> 17:56.876
I have worked
with better choirs.

17:56.909 --> 17:58.445
But I have never worked
with a choir

17:58.478 --> 18:00.813
that has made me so happy, and
that is because of one man--

18:00.847 --> 18:01.914
Our Reverend Jax.

18:01.948 --> 18:04.484
Give him a hand.
[applause]

18:04.517 --> 18:08.155
So, this year, we're
celebrating Christmas his way.

18:08.188 --> 18:12.259
[quietly] And apparently anyone
is allowed to join.

18:12.292 --> 18:16.329
all: * Joy to the world,
the Lord has come *

18:16.363 --> 18:20.500
* Let Earth receive her King

18:20.533 --> 18:22.135
* Yeah

18:22.169 --> 18:25.004
- You guys!
It's a Bollywood Christmas!

18:25.037 --> 18:28.641
* Joy to the World

18:28.675 --> 18:32.312
* The Lord has come

18:32.345 --> 18:34.581
* Let Earth
- * Let Earth

18:34.614 --> 18:36.516
- * Receive
- * Receive

18:36.549 --> 18:38.084
all:
* Her King!

18:38.117 --> 18:40.187
* Santa Claus
is coming to town *

18:40.220 --> 18:44.691
* Let every heart

18:44.724 --> 18:48.528
* Prepare Him room

18:48.561 --> 18:52.999
* You better watch out,
you better not cry *

18:53.032 --> 18:56.269
* You better not pout,
I'm telling you why *

18:56.303 --> 18:58.605
* And Heaven
- * And Heaven

18:58.638 --> 19:05.312
all: * And Heaven
and Nature sing *

19:05.345 --> 19:09.482
* Santa Claus
is coming to town! *

19:09.516 --> 19:12.719
* Joy to the world,
joy to the world! *

19:12.752 --> 19:19.226
* Santa Claus
is coming to town *

19:19.259 --> 19:21.794
- Ho, ho, ho, ho!

19:21.828 --> 19:25.532
all: * Santa Claus is coming
to town *

19:25.565 --> 19:28.901
* Joy to the world,
joy to the world *

19:28.935 --> 19:33.673
* Santa Claus
is coming to town *

19:33.706 --> 19:37.009
- Don't forget--
keep the Christ in Christmas.

19:37.043 --> 19:41.681
all:
* Santa Claus is coming

19:41.714 --> 19:43.550
* To town

19:43.583 --> 19:50.223
* Joy to the world

19:50.257 --> 19:54.193
[cheers and applause]

20:00.900 --> 20:04.371
- That service was awesome!
Is it always like this?

20:04.404 --> 20:05.872
- We try.

20:05.905 --> 20:07.674
Next week I'll be improv'ing
my sermon.

20:07.707 --> 20:10.076
Like, I'll ask for a place, and
someone will yell, "Heaven!"

20:10.109 --> 20:12.178
And then I'll, like, riff
for 30 to 40 minutes.

20:12.211 --> 20:14.881
- I'll be back for that.
- [laughs]

20:14.914 --> 20:17.884
So, uh, I know my service
was a little, uh...

20:17.917 --> 20:20.052
unorthodox.

20:20.086 --> 20:22.422
- Unorthodox, uncouth,
uncalled for...

20:22.455 --> 20:25.224
- But you did get Anjali
to come out of her shell.

20:25.258 --> 20:26.926
- So you must be doing
something right.

20:26.959 --> 20:29.629
- Boy, I'll say.
That service was so moving,

20:29.662 --> 20:31.298
it almost caused me
to doubt my atheism.

20:31.331 --> 20:32.699
- [gasps]

20:32.732 --> 20:34.767
- I'm kidding.
Merry Christmas.

20:34.801 --> 20:37.270
- I, uh--I thought
about what you said,

20:37.304 --> 20:39.472
and, uh, I'm gonna go
to the bank tomorrow

20:39.506 --> 20:41.073
and open up my own account.

20:41.107 --> 20:43.576
- Oh, well, thank you, but that
doesn't change anything.

20:43.610 --> 20:45.111
- I know.

20:45.144 --> 20:47.314
I also started a college fund
for Cash.

20:47.347 --> 20:49.482
- With what money?

20:49.516 --> 20:51.050
- Well, it turns out
that Costco

20:51.083 --> 20:52.785
picked up Dookie's towels.

20:52.819 --> 20:56.289
We made our investment back
plus a little something extra.

20:56.323 --> 20:59.559
- Well, I guess it is
Tracy Chapman's year.

20:59.592 --> 21:01.928
- Sure is.
Look at us.

21:01.961 --> 21:04.431
We made it through this
no strings attached.

21:04.464 --> 21:05.932
- [sighs]

21:05.965 --> 21:09.436
There is one tiny string.

21:09.469 --> 21:11.438
I might be pregnant.

21:11.471 --> 21:13.740
[suspenseful music]

21:13.773 --> 21:16.809
- Well...

21:16.843 --> 21:19.979
Cash won't be happy
that half his $38

21:20.012 --> 21:22.515
is going into
the baby's account, but...

21:22.549 --> 21:23.916
- [sighs]

21:23.950 --> 21:25.552
- It's only right.
